3
00:00:05,470 --> 00:00:10,130
We have some fun origami
topics today, mostly

4
00:00:10,130 --> 00:00:12,215
related to a topic
called pleat folding.

5
00:00:12,215 --> 00:00:21,830

6
00:00:21,830 --> 00:00:24,749
General idea of pleat
folding is to fold

7
00:00:24,749 --> 00:00:26,790
alternating mountains and
valleys back and forth.

8
00:00:26,790 --> 00:00:29,330

9
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:33,760
And you can do a lot of cool
things with pleat folding,

10
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:35,720
and that's what I want
to talk about today.

11
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:39,630
In particular, this
model is usually

12
00:00:39,630 --> 00:00:42,660
called the hyperbolic
paraboloid.

13
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:44,150
It's pretty simple.

14
00:00:44,150 --> 00:00:45,680
You start with a square paper.

15
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:47,660
You fold this crease
pattern, which

16
00:00:47,660 --> 00:00:49,860
is concentric squares
alternating mountain

17
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:52,080
and valley, and you
fold the diagonals,

18
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:53,600
alternating mountain and valley.

19
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,975
You crush it all
together, you'll

20
00:00:54,975 --> 00:00:56,380
get this sort of x-shape.

21
00:00:56,380 --> 00:00:58,960
And you sort of let
go, give it a twist,

22
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:05,760
and it pops into this
saddle form, which

23
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:09,245
looks a lot like a
hyperbolic paraboloid, which

24
00:01:09,245 --> 00:01:12,400
is one of the standard
saddle surfaces.

25
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:15,360
It's approximating a hyperbolic
paraboloid, we think,

26
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:19,762
or we thought, and that's
why it's called that.

27
00:01:19,762 --> 00:01:21,220
So you should all
try this at home.

28
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:22,011
It's a great model.

29
00:01:22,011 --> 00:01:22,722
It's very cool.

30
00:01:22,722 --> 00:01:24,180
It's an example of
something I like

31
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:27,390
