53
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:35,460
That's elastic memory.

54
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:39,040
If however, I crease
a piece of paper,

55
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:41,760
then that's called a
plastic deformation

56
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:44,650
beyond the yield
point of the material.

57
00:02:44,650 --> 00:02:47,689
This works in sheet metal
