61
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,930
Depending on how
hard I crease it,

62
00:02:56,930 --> 00:03:01,020
it will go to a sharper angle.

63
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:02,920
So that's basically
what's going on.

64
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:05,910
In these surfaces, where
we crease the paper,

65
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:07,560
it wants to stay bent.

66
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,950
Where we don't crease the
paper, it wants to stay flat.

67
00:03:09,950 --> 00:03:12,330
It can't do all of those
things, but physics

68
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:16,690
finds an equilibrium
among all those forces.

